cast_shell: deliver wl_touch events to blink on bridgething

CastContentWindowAura installs a TouchBlocker pre-target handler on
the WebContents native view at CreateWindow time, gated on
!params_->enable_touch_input. TouchBlocker::OnTouchEvent calls
touch->SetHandled() on every ui::TouchEvent it sees, so when the flag
is left at its mojom default (false), wl_touch dispatches that have
already cleared the CastWindowTreeHostAura gate are eaten in aura's
pre-target chain and never reach blink.

CastServiceSimple::StartInternal builds its CastWebViewParams from a
default-constructed mojom struct and only sets enabled_for_dev. Flip
enable_touch_input alongside it so the kiosk surface actually receives
touch.

Pairs with --enable-input on the launcher: that flag opens the
CastWindowTreeHostAura::DispatchEvent gate (early-returns on every
event when enable_input_ is false) and swaps the root window's
NullWindowTargeter for a real one, so events reach aura at all. This
patch then keeps them from being eaten one layer down. Either one
alone leaves hardware touch dead; together they restore taps to blink.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [kiosk-specific use case]

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>

--- a/chromecast/browser/service/cast_service_simple.cc
+++ b/chromecast/browser/service/cast_service_simple.cc
@@ -64,6 +64,11 @@
   ::chromecast::mojom::CastWebViewParamsPtr params =
       ::chromecast::mojom::CastWebViewParams::New();
   params->enabled_for_dev = true;
+  // bridgething: deliver wl_touch events to blink. CastContentWindow
+  // Aura installs a TouchBlocker pre-target handler that calls
+  // touch->SetHandled() on every ui::TouchEvent unless this is true;
+  // the mojom default is false, which silently eats hardware taps.
+  params->enable_touch_input = true;

   cast_web_view_ = web_service_->CreateWebViewInternal(std::move(params));
   cast_web_view_->cast_web_contents()->LoadUrl(startup_url_);
